1. Nisam se *brinuo* jer sam znao da ćeš ti to uspešno završiti. (I wasn't *worried* because I knew you would successfully finish it.)
2. On se *brinuo* za svoju budućnost i počeo je da uči strani jezik. (He *worried* about his future and started to learn a foreign language.)
3. *Brinuo* sam se da neću stići na vreme, ali sam ipak uspeo. (I was *concerned* that I wouldn't arrive on time, but I managed to.)
4. Kada bi samo prestao da se *brine* o sitnicama, život bi mu bio mnogo lakši. (If he just stopped *worrying* about small things, his life would be much easier.)
5. Njegova majka se uvek *brine* za njega, čak i kada je on već odrastao. (His mother always *cares* for him, even when he is already grown up.)
6. Da li si se *brinuo* da li ćeš naći posao nakon završetka fakulteta? (Did you *worry* about finding a job after finishing college?)
7. Moraš da se *brineš* o svom zdravlju i redovno vežbaš. (You have to *take care* of your health and exercise regularly.)
8. Nemoj da se *brineš* previše o tome, sve će se rešiti na kraju. (Don't *worry* too much about it, everything will be solved in the end.)
9. Kada bi se samo manje *brinula* o tome šta drugi ljudi misle o njoj, bila bi mnogo srećnija. (If she just worried less about what other people think of her, she would be much happier.)
10. Oni su se oduvek *brinuli* jedni o drugima i uvek su tu jedno za drugo. (They have always *taken care* of each other and are always there for each other.)